Despite some bad weather in the morning, the second Casterbridge Country Market for the year was well supported. With music in the background, this market offers a myriad of choices for the public. It boasts delicious snacks and something to drink, and whether you are in the market for accessories, clothing or art, you are bound to find something to your liking when browsing the stalls. ALSO READ: Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court postpones JJ Peters’ case for formal bail application again All these options are there for you to enjoy on every first Sunday of the month from 09:00 until 13:00, so be ready to make your way to the Casterbridge Lifestyle Centre next month. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram